						<summary>

						<p>This inscription records a gift of two <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for feeding two brāhmaṇas on new-moon days (<hi rend="italic">amāvāsya</hi>) by certain Nalluḻāṉ Perumāṉ of Vaḷḷivayam. The <hi rend="italic">gaṇapperumakkal</hi> (the body) of Thiruppōndai agreed to maintain it from the interest of the gold.</p>						

						</summary>
